{"metadata":{"name":"Sahih Muslim","section":{"27":"The Book of Oaths"}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":4254,"arabicnumber":"1646.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":1}},{"hadithnumber":4255,"arabicnumber":"1646.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":2}},{"hadithnumber":4256,"arabicnumber":"1646.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":3}},{"hadithnumber":4257,"arabicnumber":"1646.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":4}},{"hadithnumber":4258,"arabicnumber":"1646.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":5}},{"hadithnumber":4259,"arabicnumber":"1646.06","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":6}},{"hadithnumber":4260,"arabicnumber":"1647.01","text":"D'après Abou Hourayra (que Dieu l'agrée), l'Envoyé de Dieu (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui) a dit : Celui qui jure et qui, en jurant, a dit : \"Par Al-Lât!\", devra dire : \"Il n'y a d'autre divinité que Dieu\". Quant à celui qui dit à son camarade : \"Viens, que je parie avec toi\", il devra faire une aumône (à titre d'expiation). Celui qui fait un serment et trouve qu'il y a mieux à faire, qu'il fasse ce qu'il est mieux et expie son serment","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":7}},{"hadithnumber":4261,"arabicnumber":"1647.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":8}},{"hadithnumber":4262,"arabicnumber":"1648","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":9}},{"hadithnumber":4263,"arabicnumber":"1649.01","text":"Abou Moûsa Al-Ach'âri a dit : Je vins trouver le Prophète (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui) à la tête d'un groupe d'Al-'Ach'ariyyûn pour lui demander de nous procurer des montures. \"Par Dieu! dit-il, je ne vous procurerai pas de montures, car, je n'ai pas de quoi vous en procurer\". Nous restâmes chez lui le temps que Dieu voulut, puis, un lot de chameaux capturés lui ayant été amené, il ordonna de nous donner trois chameaux aux bosses blanches. Quand nous fûmes partis, nous dîmes : \"Dieu ne nous bénira pas, car nous sommes venus demander à l'Envoyé de Dieu (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui) de nous procurer des montures, il a juré qu'il n'en a pas et pourtant il nous les a procurés\". Nous revînmes vers le Prophète et nous lui informâmes de ce que nous avons dit, il nous répondit : \"Ce n'est pas moi qui vous en ai procuré, c'est Dieu qui l'a fait. Par Dieu! Quant à moi, s'il plaît à Dieu! Je ne ferai pas un serment et trouvant ensuite qu'il y a mieux à faire sans que je l'expie et fasse ce qu'il vaut mieux","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":10}},{"hadithnumber":4264,"arabicnumber":"1649.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":11}},{"hadithnumber":4265,"arabicnumber":"1649.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":12}},{"hadithnumber":4266,"arabicnumber":"1649.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":13}},{"hadithnumber":4267,"arabicnumber":"1649.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":14}},{"hadithnumber":4268,"arabicnumber":"1649.06","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":15}},{"hadithnumber":4269,"arabicnumber":"1649.07","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":16}},{"hadithnumber":4270,"arabicnumber":"1649.08","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":17}},{"hadithnumber":4271,"arabicnumber":"1650.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":18}},{"hadithnumber":4272,"arabicnumber":"1650.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":19}},{"hadithnumber":4273,"arabicnumber":"1650.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":20}},{"hadithnumber":4274,"arabicnumber":"1650.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":21}},{"hadithnumber":4275,"arabicnumber":"1651.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":22}},{"hadithnumber":4276,"arabicnumber":"1651.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":23}},{"hadithnumber":4277,"arabicnumber":"1651.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":24}},{"hadithnumber":4278,"arabicnumber":"1651.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":25}},{"hadithnumber":4279,"arabicnumber":"1651.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":26}},{"hadithnumber":4280,"arabicnumber":"1651.06","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":27}},{"hadithnumber":4281,"arabicnumber":"1652.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":28}},{"hadithnumber":4282,"arabicnumber":"1652.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":29}},{"hadithnumber":4283,"arabicnumber":"1653.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":30}},{"hadithnumber":4284,"arabicnumber":"1653.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":31}},{"hadithnumber":4285,"arabicnumber":"1654.01","text":"Abou Hourayra (que Dieu l'agrée) rapporte du Prophète le propos suivant : Salomon avait soixante femmes. Un jour, il a dit : \"Cette nuit, je vais coucher avec elles toutes pour que chacune devienne enceinte d'un cavalier qui combattra dans la voie de Dieu\". Aucune de ses femmes ne devint enceinte, sauf une qui mit au monde un enfant à qui manque la moitié du corps. L'Envoyé de Dieu (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui) a dit : \"Si Salomon avait ajouté (s'il plaît à Dieu), chacune de ces femmes aurait devenu enceinte d'un cavalier qui combattrait dans la voie de Dieu\". Interdiction d'insister sur un serment susceptible de nuire aux siens si ce serment ne porte pas sur une chose interdite","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":32}},{"hadithnumber":4286,"arabicnumber":"1654.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":33}},{"hadithnumber":4287,"arabicnumber":"1654.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":34}},{"hadithnumber":4288,"arabicnumber":"1654.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":35}},{"hadithnumber":4289,"arabicnumber":"1654.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":36}},{"hadithnumber":4290,"arabicnumber":"1654.06","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":37}},{"hadithnumber":4291,"arabicnumber":"1655","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":38}},{"hadithnumber":4292,"arabicnumber":"1656.01","text":"D'après Ibn 'Omar (رضي الله عنهما), 'Omar Ibn Al-Khattâb (que Dieu l'agrée) dit : \"Ô Envoyé de Dieu, au temps de l'Ignorance (période antéislamique), j'ai fait le vœu de faire une retraite pieuse pendant une nuit dans la Mosquée Sacrée\". - \"Accomplis ton vœu\", répondit le Prophète. Gravité du péché que commet un homme quand il accuse son esclave d'adultère","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":39}},{"hadithnumber":4293,"arabicnumber":"1656.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":40}},{"hadithnumber":4294,"arabicnumber":"1656.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":41}},{"hadithnumber":4295,"arabicnumber":"1656.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":42}},{"hadithnumber":4296,"arabicnumber":"1656.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":43}},{"hadithnumber":4297,"arabicnumber":"1656.06","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":44}},{"hadithnumber":4298,"arabicnumber":"1657.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":45}},{"hadithnumber":4299,"arabicnumber":"1657.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":46}},{"hadithnumber":4300,"arabicnumber":"1657.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":47}},{"hadithnumber":4301,"arabicnumber":"1658.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":48}},{"hadithnumber":4302,"arabicnumber":"1658.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":49}},{"hadithnumber":4303,"arabicnumber":"1658.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":50}},{"hadithnumber":4304,"arabicnumber":"1658.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":51}},{"hadithnumber":4305,"arabicnumber":"1658.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":52}},{"hadithnumber":4306,"arabicnumber":"1659.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":53}},{"hadithnumber":4307,"arabicnumber":"1659.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":54}},{"hadithnumber":4308,"arabicnumber":"1659.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":55}},{"hadithnumber":4309,"arabicnumber":"1659.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":56}},{"hadithnumber":4310,"arabicnumber":"1659.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":57}},{"hadithnumber":4311,"arabicnumber":"1660.01","text":"D'après Abou Hourayra (que Dieu l'agrée), Abou Al-Qâsim (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui) a dit : \"Celui qui accuse son esclave d'adultère subira la peine prescrite au Jour de la Résurrection, à moins que l'accusation ne soit vraie\". On doit donner à manger au servant de ce qu'on mange, de l'habiller comme on s'habille et de ne le pas charger de ce qu'il ne peut pas supporter","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":58}},{"hadithnumber":4312,"arabicnumber":"1660.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":59}},{"hadithnumber":4313,"arabicnumber":"1661.01","text":"Abou Dharr (que Dieu l'agrée) a dit : Un jour, un affront s'éleva entre un de mes frères (serviteurs) et moi. Comme je l'injuriai par sa mère qui était étrangère, il alla trouver le Prophète (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui) pour se plaindre. Quand je rencontrai le Prophète (paix et bénédiction de Dieu sur lui), il me dit : \"Abou Dharr, tu es un homme en qui reste encore un brin d'antéislamisme\". Je lui répondis : \"Ô Envoyé de Dieu, celui qui injurie les hommes, sera lui-même injurié par sa mère et son père\". Le Prophète a dit : \"Abou Dharr, tu es donc un homme en qui reste encore un brin d'antéislamisme : ce sont vos frères ces gens que Dieu a placés sous votre autorité. Nourrissez-les de votre nourriture, habillez-les comme vous vous habillez et ne leur imposez pas des tâches pesantes; mais, s'il vous arrive de le faire venez-leur en aide","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":60}},{"hadithnumber":4314,"arabicnumber":"1661.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":61}},{"hadithnumber":4315,"arabicnumber":"1661.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":62}},{"hadithnumber":4316,"arabicnumber":"1662","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":63}},{"hadithnumber":4317,"arabicnumber":"1663","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":64}},{"hadithnumber":4318,"arabicnumber":"1664.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":65}},{"hadithnumber":4319,"arabicnumber":"1664.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":66}},{"hadithnumber":4320,"arabicnumber":"1665.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":67}},{"hadithnumber":4321,"arabicnumber":"1665.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":68}},{"hadithnumber":4322,"arabicnumber":"1666.01","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":69}},{"hadithnumber":4323,"arabicnumber":"1666.02","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":70}},{"hadithnumber":4324,"arabicnumber":"1667","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":71}},{"hadithnumber":4325,"arabicnumber":"1501.03","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":72}},{"hadithnumber":4326,"arabicnumber":"1501.04","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":73}},{"hadithnumber":4327,"arabicnumber":"1501.05","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":74}},{"hadithnumber":4328,"arabicnumber":"1501.06","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":75}},{"hadithnumber":4329,"arabicnumber":"1501.07","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":76}},{"hadithnumber":4330,"arabicnumber":"1501.08","text":"","grades":[],"reference":{"book":27,"hadith":77}},{"hadithnumber":4331,"arabicnumber":"1502.02","text":"","grades":[